,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/2/S/25 Q23","year":2025,"session":"Specimen","tex":"Write as a single fraction in its simplest form.\n\\[\n\\dfrac{3}{x - 4} - \\dfrac{4}{x + 3}\n\\]","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2025Specimen-Paper2-Q24","paper":"2025Specimen-Paper2","qnum":24,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Coordinate geometry"],"s":"2.8","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Proportion","qtype":"proportion","g":"proportion","src":"0580/2/S/25 Q24","year":2025,"session":"Specimen","tex":"(a) Write \\quad $x^2 - 4x + 7$ \\quad in the form \\quad $(x - a)^2 + b$.\n\n(b) Write down the coordinates of the turning point of the graph of \\quad $y = x^2 - 4x + 7$.\n\n (  ,  )","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2025Specimen-Paper2-Q25","paper":"2025Specimen-Paper2","qnum":25,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.4","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Similarity and congruence","qtype":"similarity and congruence","g":"mixed","src":"0580/2/S/25 Q25","year":2025,"session":"Specimen","tex":"The two shapes are mathematically similar.\n\nThe area of the larger shape is 36\\,cm$^2$ and the area of the smaller shape is 25\\,cm$^2$.\n\nThe height of the larger shape is 9\\,cm and the height of the smaller shape is $x$\\,cm.\n\nFind the value of $x$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025Specimen-Paper2-Q26","paper":"2025Specimen-Paper2","qnum":26,"marks":11,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"2.11","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sketching curves","qtype":"sketching curves","g":"graph","src":"0580/2/S/25 Q26","year":2025,"session":"Specimen","tex":"$$\\text{f}(x) = x(x + 2)(x - 3)$$\n\n(a) On the diagram, sketch the graph of $y = \\text{f}(x)$ for $-